    {
      "name": "05 - Fault Tolerance",
      "description": "Tests for circuit breakers, rate limiting, and service isolation. Each request includes manual steps in its description that must be completed before sending the request.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[CB] Place Order — Customer Service Down",
          "description": "**Before running this request:**\n1. Stop Customer Service:\n   - Docker: `docker stop food-delivery-customer-service`\n   - Local: kill the process on port 8081\n\n**Expected behaviour:**\n- First 5 requests: HTTP 503 from CustomerClient fallback factory (circuit breaker CLOSED but calls failing)\n- After 5 failures: circuit transitions to OPEN. Calls are rejected immediately with 503 and `\"circuit breaker open: customer-service\"` in the body.\n\n**After testing:**\n```\ndocker start food-delivery-customer-service\n```\nThe circuit auto-transitions to HALF_OPEN after 5 seconds and closes after 3 successful probe calls.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Service unavailable (CB active)', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([503, 201]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 503) {",
                  "  const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Error message present', () => pm.expect(b.error || b.message).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{customerToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } },
              "raw": "{\n  \"restaurantId\": {{restaurantId}},\n  \"items\": [{ \"menuItemId\": {{menuItemId}}, \"quantity\": 1 }],\n  \"deliveryAddress\": \"CB Test Street\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/orders",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },

        {
          "name": "[CB] Create Restaurant — Customer Service Down",
          "description": "**Before running:** Stop Customer Service (same as previous request).\n\nRestaurant Service calls Customer Service via Feign to promote the owner's role. With Customer Service down, creating a new restaurant returns 503.\n\nExisting restaurant reads (search, get by ID, menu) still work — they do not depend on Customer Service.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Returns 503 when Customer Service is down', () => {",
