        {
          "name": "[429] Rate Limit — POST /api/orders",
          "description": "**Purpose:** Trigger the rate limiter on POST /api/orders (20 permits per second per gateway instance).\n\n**How to trigger:**\n1. In Collection Runner: set iterations = 25, delay = 0 ms\n2. Run this request only (deselect all others)\n3. The first 20 iterations return 201 or CB response; subsequent iterations within the same second return 429 with `Retry-After: 1` header\n\n**Expected:**\n- HTTP 429 with `Retry-After: 1` header after the bucket is exhausted",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 or 429', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 429, 503]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 429) {",
                  "  pm.test('Retry-After header present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Retry-After')).to.equal('1');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
